!! Engine identifier

This adapter registers as `MindElixir`. Use this name in:

* `$:/config/rimir/mindmap/default-engine`
* `mm.engine` on view tiddlers
* `engine="MindElixir"` on a `<$mindmap>` widget

!! Engine options (passed via `mm.options`)

|!Key |!Type |!Default |!Effect |
|`direction` |0/1/2 |2 |0=LEFT, 1=RIGHT, 2=SIDE (both sides) |
|`draggable` |boolean |true |Allow node drag-reparenting |
|`contextMenu` |boolean |true |Show mind-elixir's right-click menu |
|`toolBar` |boolean |true |Show mind-elixir's built-in toolbar |
|`keypress` |boolean |true |Bind keyboard shortcuts (Tab=child, Enter=sibling, Delete=remove, F2=rename) |

Additional mind-elixir options pass through verbatim. See [[mind-elixir docs|https://docs.mind-elixir.com]].

Example view tiddler:

```
mm.producer:  knowledge-tree
mm.args:      {"area":"llm"}
mm.engine:    MindElixir
mm.options:   {"direction":2, "draggable":true, "keypress":false}
mm.overlay:   $:/state/rimir/mindmap/views/llm/overlay
```

!! Op translation table

|!mind-elixir operation |!Emitted Op |!Notes |
|`finishEdit` |`{ op: "rename", id, label }` |Emitted when the user finishes inline editing |
|`removeNode` |`{ op: "removeNode", id }` |Explicit user delete |
|`addChild` |`{ op: "addNode", parent, node }` |New node created in canvas |
|`moveNode` |`{ op: "reparent", id, newParent }` |Drag-reparent |
|`moveNodeBefore` |`{ op: "reparent", id, newParent }` |Drag-reorder before sibling |
|`moveNodeAfter` |`{ op: "reparent", id, newParent }` |Drag-reorder after sibling |
|`beginEdit`, `selectNode`, `expandNode` |(none) |Informational, no overlay write |
|other |`{ op: "setAttr", id, key: "mx:lastOp", value: name }` |Round-trip preservation only |

!! Public method surface

|!Method |!Effect |
|`init(element, mdom, options)` |Construct, mount, bind events |
|`update(mdom)` |Replace data via mind-elixir's `refresh()` |
|`focus(id)` |Select the node in mind-elixir |
|`expand(id)` / `collapse(id)` |Toggle a branch |
|`destroy()` |Remove listeners and DOM |
|`on("op", fn)` |Subscribe to translated overlay ops |
|`on("select", fn)` |Subscribe to selection events (fn receives node id) |

